---
import PortalLayout from '../../../layouts/PortalLayout.astro';
import CoordinatePicker from '../../../components/ui/CoordinatePicker.astro';
import Tabs from '../../../components/ui/Tabs.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<PortalLayout title="Vertical Axis | Compass" currentPage="compass">

  <nav class="breadcrumb">
    <a href={`${base}/`}>Home</a>
    <span class="sep">›</span>
    <a href={`${base}/compass/`}>Compass</a>
    <span class="sep">›</span>
    <strong>III. Vertical Axis</strong>
  </nav>

  <div class="page-hero page-hero--teal">
    <div class="eyebrow">SECTION III</div>
    <h1>Vertical Axis</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Story Depth Dimensions — six layers from surface to core</p>
  </div>

  <div class="compass-content">

   <!-- ===== COORDINATE PICKER ===== -->
<div class="dimension-card dimension-card--coord-picker">
  <div class="coord-picker-card__header">
    <span class="coord-picker__icon" aria-hidden="true">⬡</span>
    <h5 class="coord-picker-card__title">Coordinate Picker</h5>
  </div>
  <p class="dimension-position">Choose position + dimension</p>
  <CoordinatePicker />
</div>


    <!-- ===== INTRODUCTION ===== -->
    <div class="section">
      <h2 id="introduction">Vertical Axis: Story Depth Dimensions</h2>
      <p>The vertical axis consists of six story depth dimensions arranged from surface to core. Each dimension represents a different depth of analysis, using specific frameworks and asking specific analytical questions.</p>

      <div class="dimension-vertical">
        <h4>Dimension Numbering Convention</h4>
        <p><strong>Surface Dimension 5</strong> (what you see first)</p>
        <p><strong>Structural Dimension 4</strong> (narrative mechanics and architecture)</p>
        <p><strong>Cognitive Dimension 3</strong> (how characters think and reason)</p>
        <p><strong>Psychological Dimension 2</strong> (character's emotional interior)</p>
        <p><strong>Archetype Dimension 1</strong> (universal primordial patterns)</p>
        <p><strong>Core Dimension 0</strong> (deepest essence)</p>
        <p style="margin-top: 16px;">Descending numbers indicate increasing depth: analyzing from Surface Dimension 5 → Core Dimension 0 means moving from surface toward core.</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Coordinate Notation</h3>
      <p>Every analysis point can be located using coordinates that combine horizontal axis <code>[Story Timeline Position]</code> with vertical axis <code>[Story Depth Dimension]</code>.</p>
      <p><strong>Standard notation:</strong> <code>[Story Timeline Position] / [Story Depth Dimension]</code></p>
      <p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>[12:00] / [Surface Dimension 5]</code> = Origin at surface level</li>
        <li><code>[6:00] / [Psychological Dimension 2]</code> = Midpoint at psychological depth</li>
        <li><code>[9:00] / [Core Dimension 0]</code> = Crisis at thematic core</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Read as:</strong> "Position [X], Dimension [Y]"</p>
      <ul>
        <li>"Position six o'clock, Psychological Dimension two"</li>
        <li>"Position nine o'clock, Core Dimension zero"</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <hr/>

    <!-- ===== DIMENSIONS ACCORDION ===== -->
    <h2 id="dimensions">The Six Dimensions</h2>

    <div class="accordion-controls">
      <button class="accordion-controls__btn" data-accordion-group="dimensions" data-action="expand" type="button">Expand All</button>
      <button class="accordion-controls__btn" data-accordion-group="dimensions" data-action="collapse" type="button">Collapse All</button>
    </div>

    <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- DIMENSION 5 — SURFACE / EXPRESSIVE -->
    <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <div class="accordion-item" data-accordion-group="dimensions">
      <details id="d5-details" open>
        <summary class="accordion-toggle accordion-toggle--teal" style="--depth-accent: var(--dim-5);">
          <span class="accordion-toggle__icon accordion-toggle__icon--teal">D5</span>
          <span class="accordion-toggle__label">
            <span class="accordion-toggle__title" id="d5-expressive">Dimension 5 — Surface / Expressive / Symbolic</span>
            <span class="accordion-toggle__meta">What you directly see and hear</span>
          </span>
          <span class="accordion-toggle__chevron">▾</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="accordion-body">

          <Tabs id="d5-tabs" accent="teal" labels={["Overview", "Framework References", "Contents", "Analysis Questions", "Use When", "Connections", "Examples"]}>

            <div slot="tab-0">
              <div class="dimension-card">
                <span class="dimension-number">SURFACE DIMENSION 5</span>
                <h3 class="dimension-title">Expressive / Symbolic</h3>
                <p class="dimension-position">What you directly see and hear</p>
                <p><strong>What This Dimension Examines:</strong> Observable phenomena — what literally appears, is said, shown, heard. The concrete surface of the story.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-1">
              <h4>Framework References</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Semiotics (Barthes, Peirce)</li>
                <li>Film craft analysis (cinematography, editing, sound)</li>
                <li>Visual symbolism catalogs</li>
                <li>Trope databases (TVTropes, etc.)</li>
                <li>Genre surface conventions</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-2">
              <h4>Contents</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Visual composition (framing, color, lighting, mise-en-scène)</li>
                <li>Dialogue (actual words spoken)</li>
                <li>Sound design (music, effects, silence)</li>
                <li>Performance (gesture, expression, movement)</li>
                <li>Editing (cuts, transitions, rhythm)</li>
                <li>Props and costumes</li>
                <li>Setting and environment</li>
                <li>Cinematography choices</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-3">
              <h4>Analysis Questions</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>What literally appears on screen?</li>
                <li>What is said/shown/heard?</li>
                <li>What visual motifs recur?</li>
                <li>What colors dominate?</li>
                <li>What objects appear repeatedly?</li>
                <li>How is space used?</li>
                <li>What is the pacing/rhythm?</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-4">
              <h4>Use When</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>First viewing/initial logging</li>
                <li>Tracking visual motifs</li>
                <li>Analyzing craft/technique</li>
                <li>Documenting concrete evidence</li>
                <li>Building observational foundation for deeper dimensions</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-5">
              <h4>Cross-Dimension Connections</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Surface manifestations always express deeper dimensions</li>
                <li>Symbols at Surface Dimension 5 point toward Archetype Dimension 1 (archetypal)</li>
                <li>Visual repetition often maps to Structural Dimension 4 (structural beats)</li>
                <li>Character behavior reveals Psychological Dimension 2 (psychological state)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-6">
              <div class="callout-example">
                <h4>Notation Example</h4>
                <p><code>[00:23:15] / [3:00] / [Surface Dimension 5]</code></p>
                <p><strong>Visual:</strong> Character crosses literal doorway, bright→dark</p>
                <p><strong>Costume:</strong> Removes outer layer (coat)</p>
                <p><strong>Sound:</strong> Ambient noise cuts to silence</p>
                <p><strong>Color:</strong> Warm tones→cool blues</p>
                <p><strong>→</strong> Threshold crossing made visible</p>
              </div>
            </div>

          </Tabs>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- DIMENSION 4 — STRUCTURAL / FUNCTIONAL -->
    <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <div class="accordion-item" data-accordion-group="dimensions">
      <details id="d4-details">
        <summary class="accordion-toggle accordion-toggle--teal" style="--depth-accent: var(--dim-4);">
          <span class="accordion-toggle__icon accordion-toggle__icon--teal">D4</span>
          <span class="accordion-toggle__label">
            <span class="accordion-toggle__title" id="d4-structural">Dimension 4 — Structural / Functional Mechanics</span>
            <span class="accordion-toggle__meta">Story architecture and narrative engineering</span>
          </span>
          <span class="accordion-toggle__chevron">▾</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="accordion-body">

          <Tabs id="d4-tabs" accent="teal" labels={["Overview", "Framework References", "Contents", "Analysis Questions", "Use When", "Connections", "Examples"]}>

            <div slot="tab-0">
              <div class="dimension-card">
                <span class="dimension-number">STRUCTURAL DIMENSION 4</span>
                <h3 class="dimension-title">Structural / Functional Mechanics</h3>
                <p class="dimension-position">Story architecture and narrative engineering</p>
                <p><strong>What This Dimension Examines:</strong> How the narrative machine functions — the engineering behind story movement, beat structure, character function assignments, and plot geometry.</p>
              </div>
              </div>

            <div slot="tab-1">
              <h4>Framework References</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>→ Section IIA (Story Structure Crosswalk) for detailed structural frameworks</li>
                <li>Three-act structure (Syd Field, McKee)</li>
                <li>Dan Harmon Story Circle (8 steps)</li>
                <li>Save the Cat (Snyder's 15 beats)</li>
                <li>Dramatica (throughlines, signposts, archetypes as functions)</li>
                <li>John Truby (22 steps)</li>
                <li>Genre conventions and expectations</li>
                <li>Plot geometry (chiastic, ring, frame, braided)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-2">
              <h4>Contents</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Act structure and turning points</li>
                <li>Beat sequences and scene functions</li>
                <li>Character function assignments (protagonist, antagonist, contagonist, etc.)</li>
                <li>Plot geometry and mirroring patterns</li>
                <li>Pacing architecture</li>
                <li>Plant/payoff chains</li>
                <li>Stakes escalation mechanics</li>
                <li>Genre beat compliance/subversion</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-3">
              <h4>Analysis Questions</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>What structural beat is this?</li>
                <li>What function does this scene serve?</li>
                <li>What is the character's structural role?</li>
                <li>How does this advance the plot mechanically?</li>
                <li>What information is being planted or paid off?</li>
                <li>How do the stakes change?</li>
                <li>What genre expectations are being met or subverted?</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-4">
              <h4>Use When</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Mapping story architecture</li>
                <li>Analyzing pacing and rhythm</li>
                <li>Diagnosing structural problems</li>
                <li>Understanding character function vs personality</li>
                <li>Comparing frameworks (how Hero's Journey maps to Save the Cat)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-5">
              <h4>Cross-Dimension Connections</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Structural beats trigger psychological shifts (Psychological Dimension 2)</li>
                <li>Mechanical functions express thematic arguments (Core Dimension 0)</li>
                <li>Character roles relate to archetypal patterns (Archetype Dimension 1)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-6">
              <div class="callout-example">
                <h4>Notation Example</h4>
                <p><code>[00:45:00] / [6:00] / [Structural Dimension 4]</code></p>
                <p><strong>Act position:</strong> End of Act 2A / Start of Act 2B</p>
                <p><strong>Function:</strong> Midpoint/Find Point</p>
                <p><strong>Beat:</strong> Character locates the object/person/truth sought</p>
                <p><strong>Story shift:</strong> From reactive→proactive</p>
                <p><strong>Character role:</strong> Protagonist + Emotion hybrid</p>
                <p><strong>Plant:</strong> Information that will pay off at 10:00</p>
                <p><strong>Stakes:</strong> Raised, ticking clock introduced</p>
                <p><strong>→</strong> Harmon: FIND step</p>
                <p><strong>→</strong> Dramatica: IC pressure peaks</p>
              </div>
            </div>

          </Tabs>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- DIMENSION 3 — COGNITIVE / LOGICAL -->
    <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <div class="accordion-item" data-accordion-group="dimensions">
      <details id="d3-details">
        <summary class="accordion-toggle accordion-toggle--teal" style="--depth-accent: var(--dim-3);">
          <span class="accordion-toggle__icon accordion-toggle__icon--teal">D3</span>
          <span class="accordion-toggle__label">
            <span class="accordion-toggle__title" id="d3-cognitive">Dimension 3 — Cognitive / Logical / Rational</span>
            <span class="accordion-toggle__meta">Thought patterns and belief systems</span>
          </span>
          <span class="accordion-toggle__chevron">▾</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="accordion-body">

          <Tabs id="d3-tabs" accent="teal" labels={["Overview", "Framework References", "Contents", "Analysis Questions", "Use When", "Connections", "Examples"]}>

            <div slot="tab-0">
              <div class="dimension-card">
                <span class="dimension-number">COGNITIVE DIMENSION 3</span>
                <h3 class="dimension-title">Cognitive / Logical / Rational</h3>
                <p class="dimension-position">Thought patterns and belief systems</p>
                <p><strong>What This Dimension Examines:</strong> How characters think, reason, distort, persuade, and defend their worldview.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-1">
              <h4>Framework References</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>→ Narrative Cognition Map: Cognitive &amp; Rhetorical Patterns section</li>
                <li>Logical fallacies (complete taxonomy)</li>
                <li>Cognitive biases (Kahneman/Tversky, heuristics)</li>
                <li>Rhetoric modes (Ethos, Pathos, Logos, Kairos, Mythos, Telos, Bios)</li>
                <li>Transactional Analysis (Parent/Adult/Child ego states)</li>
                <li>Moral Foundations Theory (Haidt)</li>
                <li>Spiral Dynamics (value systems/worldviews)</li>
                <li>Identity-protective cognition</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-2">
              <h4>Contents</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Logical fallacies employed</li>
                <li>Cognitive biases active</li>
                <li>Rhetorical modes/strategies</li>
                <li>Thought patterns and reasoning errors</li>
                <li>Ego states (Parent/Adult/Child)</li>
                <li>Moral intuitions/foundations</li>
                <li>Worldview/value systems (Spiral Dynamics)</li>
                <li>Belief structures</li>
                <li>Epistemic stance (how they know what they "know")</li>
                <li>Self-justification mechanisms</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-3">
              <h4>Analysis Questions</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>What fallacies does the character employ?</li>
                <li>What biases are influencing perception?</li>
                <li>What rhetorical mode dominates?</li>
                <li>What is the character's reasoning strategy?</li>
                <li>How does the character justify their actions?</li>
                <li>What worldview/value system is operating?</li>
                <li>What ego state is dominant?</li>
                <li>What moral foundations are activated?</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-4">
              <h4>Use When</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Understanding character reasoning</li>
                <li>Analyzing dialogue for persuasion/manipulation</li>
                <li>Tracking cognitive shifts (bias → insight)</li>
                <li>Mapping argument structures in scenes</li>
                <li>Analyzing ensemble dynamics (who thinks how)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-5">
              <h4>Cross-Dimension Connections</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Cognitive patterns emerge from psychological wounds (Psychological Dimension 2)</li>
                <li>Fallacies express thematic conflicts (Core Dimension 0)</li>
                <li>Reasoning errors drive plot mistakes (Structural Dimension 4)</li>
                <li>Rhetorical modes shape dialogue (Surface Dimension 5)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-6">
              <div class="callout-example">
                <h4>Notation Example</h4>
                <p><code>[01:15:00] / [9:00] / [Cognitive Dimension 3]</code></p>
                <p><strong>Fallacy dominant:</strong> Sunk Cost Fallacy (can't abandon plan despite evidence)</p>
                <p><strong>Bias:</strong> Confirmation bias + identity-protective cognition revealing</p>
                <p><strong>Rhetoric mode:</strong> Ethos (authority) failing → Pathos (desperation)</p>
                <p><strong>Ego state:</strong> Critical Parent → Wounded Child</p>
                <p><strong>Moral foundation:</strong> Authority/Loyalty challenged by Care/Fairness</p>
                <p><strong>Spiral Dynamics:</strong> Blue (order) → Orange (achievement) crisis</p>
                <p><strong>Worldview:</strong> "Control ensures safety" → "Control created danger"</p>
                <p><strong>Cognitive dissonance:</strong> Cannot reconcile belief with reality</p>
                <p><strong>→</strong> Thought pattern breakdown triggers psychological crisis (Psychological Dimension 2)</p>
                <p><strong>→</strong> Prepares for thematic revelation (Core Dimension 0)</p>
              </div>
              <h4>Character Differentiation</h4>
              <p>In ensemble casts, assign different cognitive signatures:</p>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Hero:</strong> Appeal to Emotion + Sunk Cost Fallacy</li>
                <li><strong>Antagonist:</strong> Appeal to Authority + False Dilemma</li>
                <li><strong>Mentor:</strong> Logos + No True Scotsman</li>
                <li><strong>Sidekick:</strong> Bandwagon Fallacy + Groupthink</li>
                <li><strong>Skeptic:</strong> Slippery Slope + Projection</li>
              </ul>
              <p>This creates distinct "thinking voices" for each character.</p>
            </div>

          </Tabs>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- DIMENSION 2 — PSYCHOLOGICAL / EMOTIONAL -->
    <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <div class="accordion-item" data-accordion-group="dimensions">
      <details id="d2-details">
        <summary class="accordion-toggle accordion-toggle--teal" style="--depth-accent: var(--dim-2);">
          <span class="accordion-toggle__icon accordion-toggle__icon--teal">D2</span>
          <span class="accordion-toggle__label">
            <span class="accordion-toggle__title" id="d2-psychological">Dimension 2 — Psychological / Emotional / Affective</span>
            <span class="accordion-toggle__meta">Internal character landscape</span>
          </span>
          <span class="accordion-toggle__chevron">▾</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="accordion-body">

          <Tabs id="d2-tabs" accent="teal" labels={["Overview", "Framework References", "Contents", "Analysis Questions", "Use When", "Connections", "Examples"]}>

            <div slot="tab-0">
              <div class="dimension-card">
                <span class="dimension-number">PSYCHOLOGICAL DIMENSION 2</span>
                <h3 class="dimension-title">Psychological / Emotional / Affective</h3>
                <p class="dimension-position">Internal character landscape</p>
                <p><strong>What This Dimension Examines:</strong> The internal landscape of character — psyche, wounds, desire, identity.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-1">
              <h4>Framework References</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>→ Narrative Cognition Map: Psychological Archetypes section</li>
                <li>Jungian archetypes (12 types, shadow, anima/animus)</li>
                <li>Enneagram (9 types, core fears, growth/stress lines)</li>
                <li>Temperament theory (4 temperaments)</li>
                <li>Attachment theory (secure, anxious, avoidant, disorganized)</li>
                <li>Lacan (mirror stage, Real/Symbolic/Imaginary)</li>
                <li>Defense mechanisms (Freudian taxonomy)</li>
                <li>Character wound systems</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-2">
              <h4>Contents</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Jungian archetype (which of 12)</li>
                <li>Shadow content (repressed material)</li>
                <li>Anima/animus dynamics</li>
                <li>Enneagram type and movement</li>
                <li>Core wound and defensive structure</li>
                <li>Attachment style</li>
                <li>Want vs Need (conscious vs unconscious desire)</li>
                <li>Defense mechanisms active</li>
                <li>Temperament under stress</li>
                <li>Identity crisis/integration moments</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-3">
              <h4>Analysis Questions</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>What is the character's core wound?</li>
                <li>What defense mechanisms are visible?</li>
                <li>What does the character want vs need?</li>
                <li>What shadow material is being projected?</li>
                <li>What attachment pattern drives relationships?</li>
                <li>How is identity being challenged?</li>
                <li>What Enneagram movement is happening?</li>
                <li>What is the internal transformation arc?</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-4">
              <h4>Use When</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Character-driven analysis</li>
                <li>Understanding motivation and desire</li>
                <li>Tracking internal transformation arcs</li>
                <li>Analyzing relationship dynamics</li>
                <li>Diagnosing why characters make choices</li>
                <li>Deep viewing (second/third pass)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-5">
              <h4>Cross-Dimension Connections</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Psychological wounds express through cognitive distortions (Cognitive Dimension 3)</li>
                <li>Internal archetypes mirror mythic patterns (Archetype Dimension 1)</li>
                <li>Character beliefs drive thematic argument (Core Dimension 0)</li>
                <li>Psychological state influences behavior/dialogue (Surface Dimension 5)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div slot="tab-6">
              <div class="callout-example">
                <h4>Notation Example</h4>
                <p><code>[01:03:42] / [6:00] / [Psychological Dimension 2]</code></p>
                <p><strong>Jungian archetype:</strong> Innocent → Hero transition</p>
                <p><strong>Enneagram:</strong> Type 9 (Peacemaker) moving toward Type 3 (growth line)</p>
                <p><strong>Temperament:</strong> Phlegmatic expressing Choleric under pressure</p>
                <p><strong>Wound:</strong> Abandonment trauma activated</p>
                <p><strong>Shadow content:</strong> Anger previously repressed now surfacing</p>
                <p><strong>Defense:</strong> Reaction formation breaking down</p>
                <p><strong>Need vs Want:</strong> Wants safety / Needs authentic self-expression</p>
                <p><strong>Belief challenged:</strong> "If I don't make waves, I'll be loved"</p>
                <p><strong>→</strong> Maximum vulnerability moment</p>
                <p><strong>→</strong> Goddess archetype appears (external helper provides mirror)</p>
              </div>
            </div>

          </Tabs>
        </div>
